SEC Freezes Assets of Firm Cited in Life Settlement Broker Case

-- B y   G r e g o r y   M o t t
-- 
2011-09-02T22:25:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/sec-freezes-assets-of-firm-cited-in-life-settlement-broker-case.html
The U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission obtained a court order freezing assets of a Los
Angeles firm accused of operating a $4.5 million scheme that
defrauded investors while purporting to broker life settlements.  The SEC announced the allegations against Daniel C.S.
Powell and his company, Christian Stanley Inc., in an e-mail
statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gregory Mott in Washington at 
 gmott1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lawrence Roberts at 
 lroberts13@bloomberg.net  